pullRequest.body:
Added a function that given a simplicial set S and a set of n-1 simplexes satisfying certain conditions, creates a morphism in SSet  from a n horn to a simplicial set S.

Included also are a series of lemmas and definitions used in this construction. In particular I define a function that takes a m-simplex in a horn, and returns the smallest 'index' of face it factors through, and give a series of lemmas related to this.

nodes.body: Thanks for this PR. And sorry for not reviewing it earlier. There is an ongoing refactor by @linesthatinterlace  of the API of order-preserving maps between various `Fin n`. I think that this refactor will allow to make these proofs a lot shorter. So please coordinate with @linesthatinterlace.

@jcommelin  Thanks for taking a look at it!

I saw some of @linesthatinterlace's recent commits regarding `Fin n`. I will see if any of that can be applied to my proofs to make them shorter.
Should still be more to come.
@jstoobysmith are you planning to continue working on this PR? If not, please feel free to close it, or label it with `please-adopt`.
This looks like stuff we want in Mathlib. What's the status?
This looks like stuff we want in Mathlib. What's the status?

@linesthatinterlace To do what I want in this pull-request I need two theorems related to succAbove and predAbove, which I've currently put in this PR.

Do you know of an existing PR which includes these theorems?
I have something very similar to this in my large PR, and in the refined version I'm working on. I'm fairly certain this can be done in more generality too.
I actually thought we already had that one but maybe we just had the castSucc version.
Ok, thanks, I'll dig into your larger PR. As far as I can tell only the castSucc version is in the main branch already: `succAbove_predAbove`

Unfortunately it's a bit of a mess. As I say I have a better version prepared with most of the lemmas but I was waiting until some of the other bits of the refactor went through to add it. I'm away house hunting for the next week but I will try to get what I have pushed so that you can look at it.

OK, I have now pushed the improved version, #10283. This contains most of the results in #9145 (I think the main one it is missing is an antitone result on `succAbove` and some related lemmas.

I am not sure the simplex category stuff will build with this as it is currently, but it should make it all a lot easier/more direct. What I would dearly like to know is if there are any lemmas you feel are missing or improvements I can make the simplicial proofs (near the bottom of the new file) as things stand.
@linesthatinterlace Thank you for this, I will merge #10283 with this PR and see how I can utilise the results. I hope your house hunting goes well!
